<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">McPherson (1980: 95).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to Jalisco in central Mexico.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Jalisco</emphasis>
: 18 km W of San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sebastián">Sebastian</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cochrane et al.</emphasis>
12053 (A, IEB, WIS); Cabo Corrientes, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. Carranza et al.</emphasis>
6133 (IEB).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Like 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cairica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea cairica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quamoclit">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. quamoclit</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species has pseudo-stipules at the base of the petiole. It is also distinguished by the bipinnatisect leaf segments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
